It’s no secret that the number of residency applications per candidate has been rising.  

In 2007, the average U.S. senior applied to 32 residency programs; the average IMG, 79.

Why?  Who benefits from “Application Fever?”

@natashaabadilla @KrisEmilyMD Programs are stuck, too.  With ‘application fever’, many programs get lots of applications from candidates who are qualified but unlikely to end up going there.  Should they decline to interview those people?  Or offer an interview - only to have it cancelled the night before?

Q: How can I help our child at home?
A: Supportive, or comfort care, is required for the flu. Encourage plenty of fluids - frequent small sips. Give appropriate doses of acetaminophen or ibuprofen. Treat symptoms, not the number that the fever reaches.

Q: How long do we keep our child out of daycare/school?
A: The CDC recommends that you stay home for at least 24 hours after your fever is gone except to get medical care or for other necessities. (Your fever should be gone without the use of a fever-reducing medicine.)

Q: When do we need to come back to the ER?
A: Your child is breathing fast, is having trouble breathing
skin color is blue or grey
will not drink liquids, is not urinating, or has no tears when they cry
flu symptoms that got better, but then came back w/ a fever, or worse cough
